Key Match Events: England were caught in two minds - whether to play for the rain or try and stall the game - initially, they wanted a quick burst of wickets to push Australia way behind on the DLS par score.
Travis Head churned out 4 wickets which hurt them very badly.
England were skyrocketing with the bat, at 202/2, targetting 500 at the halfway stage, when a dramatic collapse saw them fold up for 309.
Post-Match Reflections: Harry Brook has been named as the Player of the Summer.
Travis Head has been named as the Player of the Match and Series.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Australia will be happy to 'get away' without too much damage but they will honestly admit in secret that they need to introspect a lot into the talent pool.
While England head overseas, Australia head back home for a grand summer of their own, starting with series against Pakistan before the big one against India comes up.
